[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1D 1H pass 1S pass 2S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "8f570d06ddf5674728faffc692b10a187a5b23e905f76926553bb80e69d2d5e5"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{The bidding has been as shown.   

You don't like to take partner out of his overcalled suit without good reason. Here you have good reason. So you bid 1\S. Partner replies 2\S. What do you say next? 

You expect partner to have three trumps, but he has made a minimum bid. So you take the conservative route and pass.}

